text: Why are JITted Python implementations still slow?
I understand why interpretation overhead is expensive, but why are JITted Python implementations (Psyco and PyPy) still so much slower than other JITted languages like C# and Java?
Edit:  I also understand that everything is an object, dynamic typing is costly, etc.
However, for functions where types can be inferred, I'm not sure why this matters.
